    {
      "question": "If one root of the quadratic equation $x^2 - 8x + p = 0$ is $3$, then the value of $p$ is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "If $x = 3$ is a root, it must satisfy the equation $x^2 - 8x + p = 0$.",
          "Substitute $x = 3$ into the equation.",
          "$(3)^2 - 8(3) + p = 0$.",
          "$9 - 24 + p = 0 \\Rightarrow -15 + p = 0 \\Rightarrow p = 15$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$3^2 - 8(3) + p = 0 \\\\ 9 - 24 + p = 0 \\\\ -15 + p = 0 \\\\ p = 15$"
