    {
      "question": "If the equation $x^2 + 2(k+2)x + 9k = 0$ has equal roots, then $k$ can be:",
      "answer": "(D)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "For equal roots, $D = b^2 - 4ac = 0$.",
          "$[2(k+2)]^2 - 4(1)(9k) = 0$.",
          "$4(k^2 + 4k + 4) - 36k = 0$.",
          "$4k^2 + 16k + 16 - 36k = 0 \\Rightarrow 4k^2 - 20k + 16 = 0$.",
          "Divide by $4$: $k^2 - 5k + 4 = 0 \\Rightarrow (k-1)(k-4) = 0 \\Rightarrow k = 1, 4$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$D = [2(k+2)]^2 - 4(1)(9k) = 0 \\\\ 4(k^2 + 4k + 4) - 36k = 0 \\\\ 4k^2 + 16k + 16 - 36k = 0 \\\\ 4k^2 - 20k + 16 = 0 \\\\ k^2 - 5k + 4 = 0 \\\\ (k-1)(k-4) = 0$"
      },
